Articles.Content:
HEllo I have this problem in my game, no matter where if its at the pad, building selector or while in the vab my whole screen goes black, but not alll at once a part will turn black then spread across the screen and if I tab out and come back its fine but after a few seconds it will do it again. Anyone know the cause of this, is it like running out of memory or something? ALso I'm running version 1.0.5 since I'm not sure if I want to transfer my ksp to steam.

My mods folder

Edited April 6, 2016 by Farlander
Telling what version I use.

It's just a guess, but I would look more into the driver of your graphic card. Is it updated? While it is true that 47 mods is quite a lot, you would be able to notice if it was a bug from the lack of memory. Check your task manager to see how much ksp.exe is using.

46 minutes ago, Benoit Hage said:

It's just a guess, but I would look more into the driver of your graphic card. Is it updated? While it is true that 47 mods is quite a lot, you would be able to notice if it was a bug from the lack of memory. Check your task manager to see how much ksp.exe is using.

Well I checked the task manager and it says ksp is using 2,629,592 kbs or 2.629592 Gbs, also my graphics card isn't updated so that factor to so I'm currently downloading the update.

4 hours ago, Benoit Hage said:

It's just a guess, but I would look more into the driver of your graphic card. Is it updated? While it is true that 47 mods is quite a lot, you would be able to notice if it was a bug from the lack of memory. Check your task manager to see how much ksp.exe is using.
